 in physical properties smoke considerations streaking blend ability and the flame retardant specification two mechanisms exist in the synergistic system first is the free radical capture process that takes place in the vapor phase on combustion at a temperature of over  f the halogen forms hydrochloric or hydrobromic acid that reacts with the antimony oxide to form antimony trichloride antimony oxychloride antimony tribromide or antimony oxybromide the flame retarding action takes place in the vapor stage above the burning material it is thought that free radicals propagate the flame but the antimony trihalides or antimony oxyhalides act as free radical traps and take up free radicals they inhibit ignition and pyrolysis in the solid liquid and vapor phases   a second process occurs in a solid phase and is the char process the antimony oxide promotes the formation of char essentially carbon on the substrate which reduces volatile gas formation the barrier between the substrate and the vapor phase reduces the available oxygen to the underlying substrate the barrier effect is obtained by almost any inert additive in plastics there is a cross linking with antimony to produce a more stable thermoset polymer additionally in the solid phase the formation of sbci and sboci acts as a dehydrating agent that increases charring sometimes phosphorous compounds tcp magnesium oxide alumina trihydrate molybdic oxide zinc borate or zinc oxide are used in combination or in place of antimony oxide to reduce costs to increase char formation or to reduce smoke however the substitution of the other retardants greatly reduces the flame retardance normally rendered by antimony oxide testing of the amounts of the halogen and antimony oxide in each formulation is necessary to optimize the flame retardance and lower costs alumina trihydrate is not synergistic with halogenated flame retardants it functions as a flame retardant by the release of its water of hydration and cannot be used in high temperature processes zinc borate molybdic oxide zinc oxide and magnesium oxide can be used in conjunction with antimony oxide to augment char formation and decrease smoke replacement of the antimony oxide to meet a smoke requirement compromises the flame retardance a relationship exists between particle size and tinting strength if the particles are very fine less than  nanometers they are below the visual range and there is no tint strength however within the visual range the smaller the particle size the higher the tint strength or conversely the larger the particle size the lower the tint strength                copyright �  united states antimony corporation  web design by beaver creek consultants united states antimony corporation antimony products since        main menu    printer friendly   united states antimony corporation usac  nyse mkt uamy  is a rapidly growing natural resource company that is increasing its raw material supply of antimony from properties in mexico and third parties around the world usac has produced various antimony products since  and is a fully integrated mining transportation milling smelting and marketing company   usac operates the only significant antimony smelter in the united states and it is in a �sold out� condition the company has proven experience in underground and open pit mining flotation and gravimetric milling crushing and screening dry grinding cyanide leaching precious metal refining pyrometallurgy and marketing usac has developed proprietary technology to smelt a variety of raw materials and recover impurities such as lead arsenic bismuth mercury selenium silver and gold china supplies more than  percent of all the antimony in the world and their resources are being depleted     operations include a smelter and a precious metal refinery in montana and a smelter and three mills in mexico a larger  ton mill is being installed in mexico three mexican properties supply direct shipping ore dso or mill feed for the mexican operations the los juarez property and mill at puerto blanco are being permitted to start gold and silver production that will supplement the antimony values and identify the company as a �precious metal producer�   usac owns  of the bear river zeolite corp mine in southeast idaho that management  regards as one of the best zeolite properties in the world due to its high cation exchange capacity low sodium content hardness  uniformity high potassium content large surface area and low clay and impurity content the deposit can be mined and processed cheaper than other deposits because there is little internal or external overburden it is more than  feet thick and it is very homogeneous brz zeolite has hundreds of applications as an �environmentally friendly� material   usac headquarters thompson falls montana    copyright �  united states antimony corporation  web design by beaver creek consultants usac antimony oxide storage and handling   nyse mkt uamy  united states antimony corporation     home corporate corporate highlights corporate management financial information antimony gold silver zeolite production newsroom  corporate governance sec presentations and brochures contact antimonygeneral information antimony metal and antimony oxide world production and reserves uses of antimony antimony prices and history terminology primary antimony minerals metallurgy uses and formulations test methods for flame retardancy precautions flame retardent theory usacantimony division history of usac third party raw material supplies mexico mining operations usac production facilities usac advantage usacantimony products antimony metal antimony oxide types quality control storage handling and packaging disclaimer safety data sheets sds  lb containers  lbs or greater bulk metal ingots preciousmetals gold and silver zeolite bear river zeolite company brx     printer friendly copy antimony oxide storage and handling   during handling protective clothing and nioshmsha approved respiratory equipment should be worn dust control systems should be used throughout the handling areas sweeping should be avoided a vacuum cleaner should be used to handle spillage food and cigarettes should not be taken into work areas hands and faces should be washed before smoking eating or drinking all plant personnel should shower and change clothes before leaving the plant work clothes should be washed frequently   handling and storage should be engineered to minimize spillage additionally antimony oxide should not be stored near an acid because the mixing of antimony oxide with an acid will generate stibine gas hsb a deadly poison an msds sheet is available upon request   packing is available as follows lb bag  per pallet kg bag  per pallet  poung bulk bag on pallet metric tonne bulk bag on pallet bulk truck loads up to  pounds other packing sizes are available on a price to be determined basis            copyright �  united states antimony corporation  web design by beaver creek consultants   nyse mkt uamy  united states antimony corporation     home corporate corporate highlights corporate management financial information antimony gold silver zeolite production newsroom  corporate governance sec presentations and brochures contact antimonygeneral information antimony metal and antimony oxide world production and reserves uses of antimony antimony prices and history terminology primary antimony minerals metallurgy uses and formulations test methods for flame retardancy precautions flame retardent theory usacantimony division history of usac third party raw material supplies mexico mining operations usac production facilities usac advantage usacantimony products antimony metal antimony oxide types quality control storage handling and packaging disclaimer safety data sheets sds  lb containers  lbs or greater bulk metal ingots preciousmetals gold and silver zeolite bear river zeolite company brx     printer friendly copy management   united states antimony corpor